CGU: Common & General Use

  http://cgujs.com

Documentation

  http://docs.cgujs.com

--------------------------------

Download

  http://code.google.com/p/cgujs/downloads/list

Usage

  Download the latest release and copy to `lib/cgu.js` to a suitable location.

  <script type="text/javascript" src="/path/to/cgu.js"></script>

--------------------------------

Building

  To build CGU, you'll need:

    - A copy of the CGU source tree, by release archive or Subversion repository
    - Ruby 1.8.7 (http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/)
    - RubyGems 1.3.1 (http://www.rubygems.org/)
      - gem install rake
      - gem install jsmin

  From the source tree root directory, run either of the following:

    $ rake
    $ rake build

  For information on other rake commands:

    $ rake help

--------------------------------

